OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,FJustice Minister Jim O'Callaghan met
OL,7,Ffamilies affected by the tragedy at
OL,8,Fthe Department of Justice in Dublin on
OL,9,FThursday.
OL,11,F"I welcomed the opportunity to meet
OL,12,Ftoday with the families of those who
OL,13,Fdied in the Creeslough explosion in
OL,14,F2022," he said.
OL,16,F"I offered my deepest condolences to
OL,17,Fthe families on the loss of their
OL,18,Floved ones in such tragic and sudden
OL,19,Fcircumstances.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@FO]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,F"I listened to their individual
OL,7,Fconcerns and heard the families'
OL,8,Funderstandable need for justice and
OL,9,Fanswers.
OL,11,F"I want to thank the Creeslough
OL,12,Ffamilies and survivors for today's
OL,13,Fconstructive meeting."
OL,15,FIn a statement, Darragh Mackin of
OL,16,FPhoenix Law said the minister heard
OL,17,Fthe effect the delay to justice and
OL,18,Faccountability has had on the families.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUuD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,F"The minister has now confirmed
OL,7,Funequivocally to these families that
OL,8,Fhe will consider holding an inquest
OL,9,Fwith a senior judge or the senior
OL,10,Fcorner, something similar to
OL,11,FStardust," he told reporters outside
OL,12,Fthe department.
OL,14,F"These families have waited too long
OL,15,Ffor a decision for an independent
OL,16,Finvestigation.
OL,18,F"The ball is now in the minister's
OL,19,Fcourt to give that decision in the
OL,20,Fnear future and we warmly welcome that
OL,21,Fimminent time-frame."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@JO]vD@AOUzD@AOU}D@UO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,FAine Flanagan, whose partner Robert
OL,7,Fand five-year-old daughter Shauna died
OL,8,Fin the explosion, said: "We warmly
OL,9,Fwelcome the minister's commitment
OL,10,Ftoday to give consideration to our
OL,11,Flegal team's request for an
OL,12,Findependent investigation, in line
OL,13,Fwith Stardust, to ensure that we are
OL,14,Fnot once again trying to seek truth
OL,15,Fand answers many decades after the
OL,16,Fevent."
OL,18,FMr Mackin said Mr O'Callaghan holds
OL,19,F"the key to finding a solution".
OL,26,@pD@YOUxD@GO]{D@AOU{D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,FHe added: "That key comes in the form
OL,7,Fof an independent investigation
OL,8,Fchaired by the senior coroner or a
OL,9,FHigh Court judge, with the necessary
OL,10,Fpowers."
OL,12,FMr Mackin described an investigation
OL,13,Fas a "minimal ask" in comparison with
OL,14,F"the loss our clients have suffered".
OL,16,FHe added: "The continuing delay to
OL,17,Forder such an investigation erodes our
OL,18,Fclients' confidence in the justice
OL,19,Fsystem in Ireland.
OL,26,@nD@KOUrD@HO]uD@FOUuD@RO]vD@AOUvD@dO]xD@
OL,26,AKOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,F"Only when an independent
OL,7,Finvestigation is ordered will our
OL,8,Fclients have confidence in the system."
OL,10,FAnn Marie Boyle, whose sister
OL,11,FCatherine and nephew James died in the
OL,12,Fblast, said the families had also
OL,13,Fasked the minister to visit Donegal
OL,15,F"There is family members and there's
OL,16,Finjured people who can't come because
OL,17,Fof their injuries," she said, adding
OL,18,Fthat this was her second trip to
OL,19,FDublin to meet a justice minister.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@gO]wD@AOUyD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,F"So we would welcome him to come to
OL,7,FDonegal."
OL,9,FDonna Harper, mother of 14-year-old
OL,10,FLeona, said she felt the minister
OL,11,Flistened to them.
OL,13,FAsked about a public inquiry, she
OL,14,Fsaid: "He hasn't said yes, but he
OL,15,Fhasn't said no.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@IO]vD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775848268
OL,3,CIrish justice minister 'will consider'
OL,4,Cinquiry into Creeslough explosion
OL,6,F"He said that if there is going to be
OL,7,Fprosecutions through the courts, that
OL,8,Fhe will certainly meet us again if we
OL,9,Fstill have questions that need to be
OL,10,Fanswered, and he certainly will look
OL,11,Finto the inquiry. So he hasn't ruled
OL,12,Fit out."
OL,14,FShe added that while the families
OL,15,Fappreciate the time they were given by
OL,16,Fthe minister, it has been almost four
OL,17,Fyears since the explosion.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/11
